replies.body:
Mmmh in my opinion it's more linked to kit and item overspecialization. Tanks now all have some %health damage integrated in their kits, whereas it used to be only available on a select few (Amumu?)
Juggs have BC which has insane synergy with a lot of kits, they also had base stats reworked to go well with {{item:3053}} etc. For the most part they also have %health damage or %armor pen, to favourise fighting the frontline.
ADC itemization basically offers a solution for everything. AD menace? {{item:3026}} . AP menace? {{item:3156}} . CC menace? {{item:3139}} 
Support itemization ... Should we even talk about it? Amazing items like {{item:3504}} {{item:3190}} {{item:3107}}
Assassin itemization .. Great lethality options {{item:3147}} {{item:3142}} {{item:3814}}
Mages.. are maybe the least beneficial of this but there are still good options. 

Everyone has the items they want and their kit has been reworked to have insane synergies.

Compare to a few years ago, where the itemization was way less specialized, the kits had kinda random scalings, a bit of AD ratios, AP ratios, rarely health ratios or %health as this was extremely powerful. The most broken ratios/scalings were maybe Kog'maw (%health magic on hit) and Vayne (% health true damage) aaand that's it. And actually put them as great lategame carries because they had access to this kind of broken stat.

 Funnily enough, the fact people didn't have as much %health things and more like, base damage, made ADC's easily oneshot by anyone and kinda forced to take real defensive items like old GA/old banshees (purely defensive items at that time).
 Assassin itemization was like.. Youmuu's then brutalizer then well idk what to build... Bloodthirster? lol
